310 g Chicken Breast, Diced
½ cup Couscous
113 g Mirepoix
1 unit(s) Lemon
28 g Baby Spinach
7 g Cilantro
250 mL Crushed Tomatoes
8 g Moroccan Spice Blend
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 g Salt*
0.13 g Pepper*
½ tbsp Butter*

Before starting, to a medium pot, add half the stock powder and 2/3 cup (1 1/3 cups) water. Bring to a boil over high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Once water is boiling, stir in couscous. Remove the pot from heat, then cover and set couscous aside for 5 min to rehydrate.

Meanwhile, roughly chop cilantro.
Juice lemon.

Heat a large pot over medium-high.
While the pot heats, snip a corner of chicken packaging and drain excess liquid.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken and mirepoix. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 4-6 min, stirring often, until chicken is golden and cooked through.**
Add Moroccan Spice Blend. Cook for 30 sec, until fragrant.
Add crushed tomatoes. Cook for 4-5 min, stirring often, until stew thickens slightly. Season with salt and pepper.

Add spinach and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice. Cook for 1-2 min, until spinach wilts.
Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) butter to couscous, then fluff with a fork. Stir in half the cilantro.
Divide couscous between plates. Top with chicken stew.
Sprinkle remaining cilantro over top.